
Unit 3 Week 9 Presentation 2 Submission
Purpose of Activity

The purpose of this assignment is to provide you with an opportunity to share your progress.

It supports the following Unit Objectives:

    Finalize software implementation and begin software validation.
    Demonstrate project functionality.
    Discuss opportunities in the field of software design and development (optional).
    Conduct system and user testing.

Instructions

For this assignment, you will work as a team to create a professional and concise (10 minutes max) presentation to demonstrate your progress. The presentation should include the sections listed below:

    Update of Progress: Review requirements documentation, user stories, or product backlog and project plan.
    Project Walk-Through: Walk through the functional aspects of the project and address planned features that have not yet been programmed.
    Test Plan: Review your test plan.
    Issues: Discuss issues and strategies.
    Individual Responsibilities: Each team member should present their own tasks and plan for the completion of those tasks.

Submission Guidelines

When submitting your assignment, follow these guidelines: 

    Submit (1) a PDF of your slides and (2) a YouTube link to the presentation. Your video should be under 10 minutes.
    All cameras must be on the whole time during the recording. Please wear casual or business professional attire. (Body should be covered; no tank tops, jerseys, t-shirts, etc.)
    Each person must present. 
    Submit only one presentation per group.

